translated: Forssell, Erik, district veterinarian, Värnamo, born on August 24, 1888 in Låstad, Skaraborg County, Sweden, son of C.I.F. and Lotten Johansson. Married to Elsa Malmström in 1917. They had two children: Carl, born in 1919, and Margareta, born in 1921. Forssell obtained a degree from Linköping University in 1908 and became a certified veterinarian in 1913. He worked as a district veterinarian in the county of Skaraborg from 1914 to 1923 and in Värnamo from 1923 onwards. Forssell served as chairman of the Silite Health Committee from 1918 to 1922 and of the Värnamo Health Committee since 1925.
